                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="sole" script="syr-Syre" medium="">
                        <desc>This manuscript is written in a good, regular Estrangela.</desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p/>
                     <list>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="" to=""/>
                           <p>A summary of the contents, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܩ̈ܦܠܐܐ
                                 ܕܒܪܝܬܐ</foreign>, is prefixed, fol. 2a [ <bibl>See Chrysostom,
                                 Synopsis Scripturae Sacrae ; Opera, ed. 1834-8, t. vi. p. 373;
                                 Migne, Patrol. Gr., t. lvi., col. 317, and Ceriani in the work
                                 cited above, t. ii. fasc. i. p. xiii</bibl>.]</p>
                           <p><quote xml:lang="syr"/></p>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="" to=""/>
                           <p>Several portions of the capitula are missing, as also the following
                              passages of the text: ch. i. 1—iv. 8, ix. 24— xvi. 2, xvi. 12 — xx. 1,
                              xx. 13 — xxxi. 53, xxxii. 12 — xxxvi. 2, xl. I8 — xliii. 1, and xlvii.
                              16—1. 17. </p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="46b" to=""/>
                           <p>Subscription.</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr-Syre">ܫܠܡ ܟܬܒܐ ܕܒܪܝܬܐ̣. ܐܝܟ ܡܫܠܡܢܘܬܐ ܕܫܒܥܝܢ
                                 ܘܬܪ̈ܝܢ</quote>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="" to=""/>
                           <p>The lessons are rubricated in the text, the end of each being
                              indicated by <foreign from="syr">ܫ</foreign>. In the <foreign
                                 from="syr">ܩ̈ܦܠܐܐ</foreign> they are noted on the margins.</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="" to=""/>
                           <p>The text exhibits the critical marks of the <bibl>Hexapla</bibl> of
                                 <persName>Origen</persName>; and the margins contain the various
                              readings of <persName>Aquila</persName> (<foreign xml:lang="syr"
                                 >ܐ</foreign>), <persName>Symmachus</persName> (<foreign from="syr"
                                 >ܣ</foreign>), and <persName>Theodotion</persName> (<foreign
                                 from="syr">ܬ</foreign>)</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="" to=""/>
                           <p>There are glosses upon some words (e. g. <locus from="24a">foll. 24
                                 a</locus>, <locus from="25a">25 a</locus>, <locus from="27b">27
                                 b</locus>, <locus from="29a">29 a</locus>, <locus from="30a">30
                                 a</locus>, etc.)</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="" to=""/>
                           <p>There a good many Greek vocables, written in not inelegant
                              characters.</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="" to=""/>
                           <p>The tetragrammaton is expressed by <foreign xml:lang="syr"
                                 >ܦܝܦܝ</foreign>.</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="" to=""/>
                           <p>The fly-leaf, fol. 1, has on the one side the word <foreign
                                 xml:lang="syr">ܬܠܝܬܝܘܬܐ</foreign> in large open letters; and on the
                              other side, a rudely drawn portrait of a saint, with some almost
                              effaced lines of modern writing beneath.</p>
                           <p>
                              <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                           </p>
                        </item>
                     </list>
